Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.51,0:00:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With just three days remaining before the serial murder case expired...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.22,0:00:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A criminal psychologist by the name of Hiramune\NDouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} repeatedly provoked the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.31,0:00:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was later found murdered at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.85,0:00:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On his back was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.06,0:00:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A wound in the form of a Z.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.90,0:00:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the bodies of the serial killer's three previous victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.86,0:00:24.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were the letters E S W in that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.53,0:00:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Haibara and Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} saw someone suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.41,0:00:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And mentioned that he had been whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.62,0:00:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police concluded the serial killer had struck again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to visit the bereaved families of the victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.59,0:00:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We accompanied Detective Takagi as he interviewed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.96,0:00:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was then that we discovered that the\Nconnection between the four victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.30,0:00:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually just mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.80,0:00:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.55,0:00:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll uncover your true face without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.57,0:00:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is eternal, labyrinths are mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.54,0:00:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturday nights are for mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.86,0:00:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi has enthusiastically gone into a pitfall!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.99,0:01:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An emergency development of love and mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.66,0:01:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.41,0:01:07.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.27,0:02:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do recognize these gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.98,0:03:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were frequent customers that would\Nalways share a table, quite a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brings back memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.90,0:03:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.20,0:03:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the criminal psychologist, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.03,0:03:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This picture is from twenty years later, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.91,0:03:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must be the student that would always play with those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.37,0:03:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're saying those four did play mahjong here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.42,0:03:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every Saturday night at 10:00 PM, always these four.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.46,0:03:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was the doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.59,0:03:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The associate professor of science and engineering...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.51,0:03:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The beginning lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.80,0:03:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the criminal psychology university student.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.18,0:03:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a gap in their ages, but they had things in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.81,0:03:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would often discuss and reason\Nthrough cases over games of mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.23,0:03:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The culprit was the husband that was interviewed."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.28,0:03:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The trick utilized his expert medical knowledge."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.15,0:03:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crazy thing was that they were usually right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you asking about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.54,0:03:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, by the same criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.37,0:04:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.33,0:04:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All four at once!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.38,0:04:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the first was twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.05,0:04:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't kept an eye on the news for a long time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only checked the cases that those four mentioned in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I only bought the paper for those two years they were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.06,0:04:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they stopped coming, I no longer bought them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.10,0:04:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stopped coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.60,0:04:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.61,0:04:28.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't hear it very well, but they mentioned a "complete crime."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, the student was the only one who would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.95,0:04:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would sit down at a table alone and polish tiles all by his lonesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.12,0:04:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they were killed, the culprit was likely that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.87,0:04:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying you have a lead!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.71,0:04:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a customer that was always\Nannoyed at the deductions of those four.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.05,0:04:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After everyone else stopped coming, that one man\Nwould always tease the lonesome student...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It even resulted in a big fight between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.14,0:05:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember him yelling at one point...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.64,0:05:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm gonna do something about all of you!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.48,0:05:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And could you please tell us who that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.65,0:05:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.77,0:05:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a reputation as being bad, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there was that incident where that gun disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.78,0:05:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When a police officer left his police box open...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His handgun ended up disappearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.33,0:05:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it caused quite a stir,\Nit was returned within two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.54,0:05:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were rumors that that customer was responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And back during their fight, this case of tiles was scattered about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.97,0:05:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the damage, they couldn't be used anymore, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And those mahjong tiles were thrown by that customer as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.18,0:05:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.14,0:05:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cleaned up the tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.02,0:05:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.15,0:05:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the police came to stop the fight and took those two\Naway, I picked them up and collected them all in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.69,0:05:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're saying that the only fingerprints on those tiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Belong to you, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:05:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that one other customer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.87,0:06:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just observing for a social studies class...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, if those two were hauled in by the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should still be records of it somewhere, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.59,0:06:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll take these damaged mahjong tiles along with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your fingerprints as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, now that you mention it, I got a weird call last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A guy asked if a doctor, an associate professor, a lawyer,\Nand a criminal psychology student all used to play here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.61,0:06:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've found a lead to the suspect in the serial killer case?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.53,0:06:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twenty years ago, the suspect got in an argument with\NHiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and was restrained in a police box!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Address and occupation unknown...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.33,0:06:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.67,0:06:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kibo Dokurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kibo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.67,0:06:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say Kibo Dokurou!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kibo"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.30,0:06:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that burglar-murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:07:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fairly certain he was just discharged from prison a\Nfew days ago after a fifteen year prison stint, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.01,0:07:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the serial murders stopped during those fifteen years...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.27,0:07:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was incarcerated for that period and was unable to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.60,0:07:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.90,0:07:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.23,0:07:14.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We must find this man at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.57,0:07:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring him before me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.28,0:07:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he's really enthusiastic about this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.99,0:07:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.28,0:07:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he found a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.91,0:07:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard some occasional rumors to that effect...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be sure that he's on his guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.96,0:07:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see it in movies and dramas?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.71,0:07:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll make a careful promise to his wife or lover...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.17,0:07:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then end up taking a bullet of misfortune\Nfrom a suspect, dying in the line of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, those—they're just stories, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morimura fell victim to it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had planned to marry the very next month...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.27,0:07:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, to impress the woman, he acted on a whim of haste...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.28,0:07:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was run over by the suspect's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.78,0:07:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.57,0:08:00.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.37,0:08:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Age has brought my time on as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This scar...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.16,0:08:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It reacted when I heard someone had met the suspect in a sauna.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.83,0:08:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was even more pain when I walked\Ninto the crime scene of the fourth victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, with only a few hours behind us,\Nit's as if it has all come to an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.01,0:08:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the pain is long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be heaven signaling to me, saying that my work here is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.06,0:08:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.48,0:08:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking you had investigated quickly, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was helping from the shadows, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.15,0:08:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.86,0:08:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that means the hot springs trip is off, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go with him to the hot springs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.66,0:08:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He still found the culprit, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.87,0:08:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so narrow-minded!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.54,0:08:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I cannot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.60,0:08:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Personal feelings are not permitted in investigations!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.71,0:08:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had almost forgot...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just one mistake in this line of work can mean death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll take these kids home in my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You go accompany Chiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others in the search for Kibo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.18,0:09:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.18,0:09:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Satou speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.86,0:09:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already got Kibo!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.32,0:09:20.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he was found in his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.07,0:09:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He decided to come along voluntarily...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.70,0:09:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we need to get the son of the first\Nvictim Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's to identify his voice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.74,0:09:32.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He heard the voice of the suspect as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.04,0:09:32.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.87,0:09:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.21,0:09:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you get Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.25,0:09:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe he was captured so easily, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.09,0:09:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.89,0:09:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought we would be out on an exciting chase after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.56,0:09:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least a gun fight, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.02,0:09:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You only see that in movies and dramas!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.23,0:09:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In reality, it's pretty plain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.48,0:09:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're looking bleak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.06,0:10:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Z on Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s back is what's bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:04.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As for as the three previous victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.33,0:10:05.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Their bodies had...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:08.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,E S W carved into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:10.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The last letter should be N, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.41,0:10:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that there was no pattern at all, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.21,0:10:21.17,Signs,,0,0,0,,Touzai (East/West)\N\NNanboku (South/North)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.21,0:10:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's Touzai Nanboku...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be E S W N...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:21.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead E W S N.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.51,0:10:22.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:25.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If it were mahjong, ton nan shaa pei would work, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.73,0:10:28.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All we can cover right now E S W.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:30.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why would the last letter be a Z?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.18,0:10:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer could have just planned to\Nposition the body sideways, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.77,0:10:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you rotate a Z, you get an N.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if that's so, it makes you wonder\Nwhy he didn't leave it sideways, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.57,0:10:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another point of concern...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.40,0:10:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would be the Ctrl key being covered with Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, the control key, along with the C key.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though pressing those two keys results in the copy function...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.79,0:10:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he need to grasp onto the mouse cord?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.58,0:11:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mouse"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.00,0:11:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to operate a PC, you need to\Nhave that round device plugged in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.09,0:11:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cord running from it resembles a mouse tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it's known as a mouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.01,0:11:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.31,0:11:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he caught the tail of a mouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.10,0:11:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person must be a cat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.06,0:11:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you don't have to say it in such a cute way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.73,0:11:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:23.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.73,0:11:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be laughing about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.70,0:11:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.91,0:11:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.99,0:11:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.95,0:11:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial murders came to an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.16,0:11:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.58,0:11:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You gotta help me here, Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.08,0:11:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been behind bars for fifteen years and just now finally got out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no desire to kill anyone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think this is our man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.43,0:11:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the one who heard the suspect's\Nvoice back then was Nabei Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.10,0:11:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should wait until he can confirm it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.06,0:11:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Megure...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.44,0:11:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you handle it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.27,0:12:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the officer that put a big scar on your\Nback long ago appeared in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.57,0:12:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.90,0:12:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that guy passed by me just a minute ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't even raise an eyebrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.62,0:12:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that this Kibo Dokurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.16,0:12:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kibo Dokurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.25,0:12:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the serial killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.54,0:12:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the victim today was that criminal psychologist, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that he was acquainted with the real suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.88,0:12:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, since those two had been involved in a fight long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine they would agree to meet in that room together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.81,0:12:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.68,0:12:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.10,0:12:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A message that said his killer was not actually the serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.82,0:12:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the blood on the Ctrl and C keys, he meant "copy."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.65,0:12:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by holding onto the mouse cord...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.41,0:12:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was referring to the cat holding the mouse's tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.49,0:12:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we combine them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.45,0:12:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Copycat."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.62,0:13:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the one who killed him trying to\Nbe the serial killer was just that—an imitator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.46,0:13:19.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,mouhou han
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.46,0:13:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An imitator!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.00,0:13:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it like mixed boiled rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.05,0:13:14.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,100)}maze gohan
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.92,0:13:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a blue birthmark on a baby's bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.38,0:13:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not an imitator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What they mean by imitator...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.81,0:13:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is an offender that copies another criminal's methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is it a cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.77,0:13:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's simply because a kitten always tries to imitate the mother cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.98,0:13:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} know that it was an imitator?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's simply because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murdered Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.24,0:13:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Happens to be the original serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.62,0:13:45.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you consider that, it makes perfect sense\Nas to why a Z was carved into his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.79,0:13:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to Superintendent Matsumoto, the serial killer\Nhad a big 1-shaped scar on his back from a katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.30,0:13:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To cover that scar...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.18,0:14:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to not let anyone discover that Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.39,0:14:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had to come up with a letter of the alphabet that would fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.10,0:14:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.77,0:14:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By doing this, he is able to camouflage the murder\Nas one committed by the serial killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.86,0:14:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If all went well, the police would continue\Nchasing an already deceased serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.03,0:14:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the real murderer would never be suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.37,0:14:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.20,0:14:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.20,0:14:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That copycat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.08,0:14:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they knew about the whistling habit...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.29,0:14:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was someone close to one of the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.13,0:14:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.55,0:14:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the light is still on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.26,0:14:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.93,0:14:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the police officer that was here earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.94,0:14:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you come to the station with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the victims' family members knew about\Nthe letters being cut into the bodies, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.33,0:15:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for those that knew about the whistling and mahjong references...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.75,0:15:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.51,0:15:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the one who heard the crime in\Nhis house as a child, Nabei Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.34,0:15:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.22,0:15:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also knew the voice of the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.39,0:15:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that he heard the voice and tone of\NHiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on TV, and remembered it by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That made him go searching for the\Nmahjong parlor his father had visited...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.06,0:15:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is how he found out how the other\Nthree had been connected to Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.65,0:15:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he was convinced Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.74,0:15:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it took him fifteen years to come to that conclusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could mean Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did not become familiar\Nwith mahjong terminology until adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.96,0:15:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.37,0:15:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the really angry person we went to visit earlier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.42,0:15:54.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person—just now, Detective Takagi went to...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.55,0:16:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're the cop they've got looking into the serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you brought a gun along, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.43,0:16:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the reason you came alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.81,0:16:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is because no one realized I was the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.86,0:16:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "culprit"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.98,0:16:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.90,0:16:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be that you killed your father fifteen years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was all Hiramune's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.41,0:16:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just taking out vengeance for my father today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.79,0:16:28.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I just remembered something about my father's murder."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.37,0:16:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I wanted to run it by a criminal psychologist\Nsuch as yourself before going to the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.17,0:16:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right over the phone, the meeting was set.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.80,0:16:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never expected I was coming for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.18,0:16:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With just a little convincing, he felt like talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive for murdering my father was apparently\Nthe "complete crime" that came up during mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.40,0:16:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about whether it would be possible to steal\Na gun from the police without anyone taking notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:16:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They had differing opinions, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.19,0:17:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune decided to prove to them he\Ncould really pull off a complete crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He expected them to praise him, but instead, the doctor\Nand professor said that the crime stops at mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He grew afraid that they would reveal the truth and\Nruin his future, so he did something about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.92,0:17:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father stayed quiet, since he knew it was his\Njoking around that encouraged him to try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.72,0:17:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some five years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.05,0:17:31.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father suggested that they turn themselves into\Nthe police, so his mouth had to be silenced as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.27,0:17:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.02,0:17:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we take off in your patrol car, they'll get me sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.28,0:17:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:44.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My cellphone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.03,0:17:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lookie here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.03,0:17:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a call from your girlfriend, Cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.16,0:17:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.24,0:17:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have her come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She can be my hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.37,0:17:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I do manage to get away, I'll set her free.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.75,0:18:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry and answer it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.17,0:18:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not that I need to tell you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you say anything fishy, I'll use the gun and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.76,0:18:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems I broke my cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to hostages, I guess it'll just be me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.81,0:18:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.61,0:18:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.44,0:18:20.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is Nabei Eiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.23,0:18:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.11,0:18:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If nothing else, he's at least responsible for killing Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.20,0:18:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi was en route to pick him up, but I can't seem to contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.12,0:18:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and send back-up, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.91,0:18:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is to all investigators!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.71,0:18:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move to the house of Nabei Eiki immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.71,0:18:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly likely he is now in possession of Takagi's handgun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.67,0:18:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take absolute caution there's little time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.05,0:18:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any minute could cost our man his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.44,0:18:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:18:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do I look like a moron to you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.61,0:19:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.07,0:19:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.33,0:19:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, they must have...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figured it all out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.87,0:19:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.75,0:19:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.33,0:19:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I rush him now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.68,0:19:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.64,0:19:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.36,0:19:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.45,0:19:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a common pattern in movies and dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.20,0:19:51.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because of the hot springs promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.29,0:19:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} have to die for it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.08,0:19:57.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.87,0:19:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.59,0:20:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.96,0:20:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He happened to put this material evidence in his chest pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.84,0:20:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, following the pattern, the criminal's bullet landed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mahjong tile...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.72,0:20:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.14,0:20:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He put it in his chest pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} rushing at Nabei Eiki and getting shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.27,0:20:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the other officers came out just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.53,0:20:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of him, this case only had one victim in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.53,0:20:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.63,0:20:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since they finished treatment, he's been in the ward...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.70,0:20:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sound asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.37,0:22:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that song he was whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.41,0:22:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The author had written, "This is how it has\Nto be," which had always reminded him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.63,0:22:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, in order to remember those Saturday night deduction battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.67,0:22:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune Douji would reminisce while whistling that tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.93,0:22:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what Superintendent Matsumoto said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.97,0:22:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.64,0:22:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, oh well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.14,0:22:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're injured, I guess we have to cancel the hot springs trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.31,0:22:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean the deal was still valid!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.11,0:22:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.36,0:22:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looked like you really gave it your all, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.74,0:22:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.41,0:22:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.78,0:22:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It always ends like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.08,0:22:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.75,0:22:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time during the bombing case...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.17,0:22:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the time during the Hammer Man case...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.33,0:22:49.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's always so close...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.80,0:22:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which room is Takagi's?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.34,0:22:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe it's 304.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.60,0:22:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.76,0:23:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.06,0:23:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what do you mean by "so close"?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.98,0:23:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.15,0:23:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just interruptions...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.02,0:23:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.73,0:23:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi just took his medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.82,0:23:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's fast asleep in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.66,0:23:20.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it's best...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.50,0:23:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To not wake him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.08,0:23:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would like him to recover, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.08,0:23:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.46,0:23:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we can come back later, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.92,0:23:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.15,0:23:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll definitely take us to the hot springs with them now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.49,0:23:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Definitely!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.03,0:23:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think that's likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.99,0:24:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that spooky house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.91,0:24:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently there's some strange guy living in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.58,0:24:09.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems we need to scout out that house, like the police would.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.79,0:24:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we are the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.25,0:24:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about the nameplate on the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.76,0:24:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.01,0:24:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they move into such a spooky house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.14,0:24:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.10,0:24:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every mystery deserves to be solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.41,0:24:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.26,0:24:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nameplate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.79,0:24:55.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.02,0:24:51.32,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The nameplate at my house says "Yoshida"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.36,0:24:52.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What about you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.24,0:24:53.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, I guess it's Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.53,0:24:55.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's a freeloader.
